          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used for private performance of rites and vows (vratas) and particularly mothers for the welfare (saubhāgya) and good fortune of their children. Includes prescriptions for the veneration of several deities, including especially Gaurī (a form of Pārvatī), Gaṇeśa, and Śiva.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Gajagaurīvrata</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName>Timaṇabhaṭa ( son of Aināpurakara Rāmabhaṭa)</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīskaṃdapurāṇe sanātangāṃdhārīsaṃvād[e ga]jagaurīvrataṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // 47 // cha // aināpurakararāmabhaṭasya putratimaṇabhaṭeṇa likhitaṃ // śrīrastu // cha // cha // gajagaurīvratasaṃpūrṇaśrīkṛṣṇārpaṇam astu śrīrastu // cha // (f. 8r).</colophon>
